# Python Code Generation Rules
- Python Version: 3.7.3
- I/O: import sys; input=sys.stdin.read().split(); it=iter(input);
- Use next(it) for all inputs.
- Strictly NO try-except blocks.
- Arrays must be 1-indexed (e.g., list size n+1).
- Keep variable names short and concise.
不要这种 if not data: exit() 判断